.TH "vmmouse_report_button" 9 "vmmouse_report_button" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmmouse_report_button \- report button state on the correct input device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" vmmouse_report_button
.BI "(struct psmouse *psmouse "  ","
.BI "struct input_dev *abs_dev "  ","
.BI "struct input_dev *rel_dev "  ","
.BI "struct input_dev *pref_dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int code "  ","
.BI "int value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "psmouse" 12
Pointer to the psmouse struct
.IP "abs_dev" 12
The absolute input device
.IP "rel_dev" 12
The relative input device
.IP "pref_dev" 12
The preferred device for reporting
.IP "code" 12
Button code
.IP "value" 12
Button value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Report \fIvalue\fP and \fIcode\fP on \fIpref_dev\fP, unless the button is already
pressed on the other device, in which case the state is reported on that
device.
